         <abstract>
            <p>A minimum-variance methodology (which, by definition, results in minimum-risk hedge ratios) does not produce minimum-uncertainty hedge ratios. This seeming dichotomy arises because regression-based methodologies result in effective interest rates that are path-dependent. In contrast, under appropriate assumptions, a value-of-a-basis-point methodology will produce an outcome that is not path-dependent.</p>
          </abstract>
